A woman has been stabbed in the neck during a robbery at a house in Uvongo, KwaZulu-Natal on Thursday. Netcare’s Nick Dollman said, “It is alleged that a female victim woke up during the house robbery and was then attacked and stabbed. None of the other family members were injured”. “She was seriously injured after being stabbed in the neck. Once stabilised, she was transported by a Netcare 911 ambulance to the hospital for further assessment and care,” said Dollman. The police are investigating the incident and no arrests have yet been made. -TNA Reporter